# Pack It Up — Cursor Rules

**`AGENTS.md` at repo root is the single full rulebook** (file map, BedroomSlice.jsx section map, sprite patterns, AI-team roles). Read it before structural work. The hard rules, inline because they break the game:

- Game code goes in `BedroomSlice.jsx` only — no new game-feature files
- No Tailwind, no Radix/shadcn/UI libraries — inline styles + canvas only
- Do NOT import: react-query, wouter, framer-motion, recharts, zod
- Layout tweaks → edit `layout.json`, not BedroomSlice.jsx
- Do NOT split BedroomSlice.jsx
- Game code stays inside `artifacts/pack-it-up/`; communal docs you may update: `FINISH_PLAN.md`, `HANDOFF.md`, `DEVLOG.md`, `docs/sessions/`, `docs/ai-team/teams/cursor/`

## Cursor team

You are probably **Grok 4.5** (team lead, commit authority in Cursor) or **Composer 2.5** (intern — tiny scoped edits, never leads commits). Onboarding: `docs/ai-team/teams/cursor/start-here.md`. Work on the standing **`cursor`** branch: pull `main` into it first, merge back to `main` at session end with a signed DEVLOG entry (`## <date> — [Cursor / <model>]`). Close out per `docs/ai-team/end-here.md`.
